{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"A few months ago,"},{"time":2000,"text":"a 40 year-old woman came to an emergency room"},{"time":5000,"text":"in a hospital close to where I live,"},{"time":7000,"text":"and she was brought in confused."},{"time":9000,"text":"Her blood pressure was an alarming"},{"time":11000,"text":"230 over 170."},{"time":14000,"text":"Within a few minutes, she went into cardiac collapse."},{"time":17000,"text":"She was resuscitated, stabilized,"},{"time":20000,"text":"whisked over to a CAT scan suite"},{"time":22000,"text":"right next to the emergency room,"},{"time":24000,"text":"because they were concerned about blood clots in the lung."},{"time":27000,"text":"And the CAT scan revealed"},{"time":29000,"text":"no blood clots in the lung,"},{"time":31000,"text":"but it showed bilateral, visible, palpable breast masses,"},{"time":36000,"text":"breast tumors,"},{"time":38000,"text":"that had metastasized widely"},{"time":40000,"text":"all over the body."},{"time":42000,"text":"And the real tragedy was, if you look through her records,"},{"time":45000,"text":"she had been seen"},{"time":47000,"text":"in four or five other health care institutions"},{"time":49000,"text":"in the preceding two years."},{"time":51000,"text":"Four or five opportunities"},{"time":53000,"text":"to see the breast masses, touch the breast mass,"},{"time":55000,"text":"intervene at a much earlier stage"},{"time":58000,"text":"than when we saw her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60000,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":62000,"text":"that is not an unusual story."},{"time":64000,"text":"Unfortunately, it happens all the time."},{"time":67000,"text":"I joke, but I only half joke,"},{"time":69000,"text":"that if you come to one of our hospitals missing a limb,"},{"time":72000,"text":"no one will believe you till they get a CAT scan, MRI"},{"time":75000,"text":"or orthopedic consult."},{"time":77000,"text":"I am not a Luddite."},{"time":79000,"text":"I teach at Stanford."},{"time":81000,"text":"I'm a physician practicing with cutting-edge technology."},{"time":83000,"text":"But I'd like to make the case to you"},{"time":85000,"text":"in the next 17 minutes"},{"time":87000,"text":"that when we shortcut the physical exam,"},{"time":91000,"text":"when we lean towards ordering tests"},{"time":93000,"text":"instead of talking to and examining the patient,"},{"time":96000,"text":"we not only overlook simple diagnoses"},{"time":99000,"text":"that can be diagnosed at a treatable, early stage,"},{"time":102000,"text":"but we're losing much more than that."},{"time":104000,"text":"We're losing a ritual."},{"time":106000,"text":"We're losing a ritual that I believe is transformative, transcendent,"},{"time":109000,"text":"and is at the heart"},{"time":111000,"text":"of the patient-physician relationship."},{"time":113000,"text":"This may actually be heresy to say this at TED,"},{"time":116000,"text":"but I'd like to introduce you"},{"time":118000,"text":"to the most important innovation,"},{"time":120000,"text":"I think, in medicine"},{"time":122000,"text":"to come in the next 10 years,"},{"time":124000,"text":"and that is the power of the human hand --"},{"time":126000,"text":"to touch, to comfort, to diagnose"},{"time":129000,"text":"and to bring about treatment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131000,"text":"I'd like to introduce you first to this person"},{"time":134000,"text":"whose image you may or may not recognize."},{"time":136000,"text":"This is Sir Arthur Conan Doyle."},{"time":138000,"text":"Since we're in Edinburgh, I'm a big fan of Conan Doyle."},{"time":141000,"text":"You might not know that Conan Doyle went to medical school"},{"time":143000,"text":"here in Edinburgh,"},{"time":145000,"text":"and his character, Sherlock Holmes,"},{"time":147000,"text":"was inspired by Sir Joseph Bell."},{"time":150000,"text":"Joseph Bell was an extraordinary teacher by all accounts."},{"time":153000,"text":"And Conan Doyle, writing about Bell,"},{"time":156000,"text":"described the following exchange"},{"time":158000,"text":"between Bell and his students."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160000,"text":"So picture Bell sitting in the outpatient department,"},{"time":163000,"text":"students all around him,"},{"time":165000,"text":"patients signing up in the emergency room"},{"time":167000,"text":"and being registered and being brought in."},{"time":170000,"text":"And a woman comes in with a child,"},{"time":172000,"text":"and Conan Doyle describes the following exchange."},{"time":175000,"text":"The woman says, \"Good Morning.\""},{"time":179000,"text":"Bell says, \"What sort of crossing did you have"},{"time":182000,"text":"on the ferry from Burntisland?\""},{"time":185000,"text":"She says, \"It was good.\""},{"time":187000,"text":"And he says, \"What did you do with the other child?\""},{"time":190000,"text":"She says, \"I left him with my sister at Leith.\""},{"time":193000,"text":"And he says,"},{"time":195000,"text":"\"And did you take the shortcut down Inverleith Row"},{"time":197000,"text":"to get here to the infirmary?\""},{"time":199000,"text":"She says, \"I did.\""},{"time":201000,"text":"And he says, \"Would you still be working at the linoleum factory?\""},{"time":205000,"text":"And she says, \"I am.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":207000,"text":"And Bell then goes on to explain to the students."},{"time":209000,"text":"He says, \"You see, when she said, 'Good morning,'"},{"time":212000,"text":"I picked up her Fife accent."},{"time":214000,"text":"And the nearest ferry crossing from Fife is from Burntisland."},{"time":217000,"text":"And so she must have taken the ferry over."},{"time":220000,"text":"You notice that the coat she's carrying"},{"time":222000,"text":"is too small for the child who is with her,"},{"time":225000,"text":"and therefore, she started out the journey with two children,"},{"time":228000,"text":"but dropped one off along the way."},{"time":231000,"text":"You notice the clay on the soles of her feet."},{"time":233000,"text":"Such red clay is not found within a hundred miles of Edinburgh,"},{"time":237000,"text":"except in the botanical gardens."},{"time":239000,"text":"And therefore, she took a short cut down Inverleith Row"},{"time":242000,"text":"to arrive here."},{"time":244000,"text":"And finally, she has a dermatitis"},{"time":246000,"text":"on the fingers of her right hand,"},{"time":248000,"text":"a dermatitis that is unique"},{"time":250000,"text":"to the linoleum factory workers in Burntisland.\""},{"time":253000,"text":"And when Bell actually strips the patient,"},{"time":255000,"text":"begins to examine the patient,"},{"time":257000,"text":"you can only imagine how much more he would discern."},{"time":260000,"text":"And as a teacher of medicine, as a student myself,"},{"time":263000,"text":"I was so inspired by that story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265000,"text":"But you might not realize"},{"time":267000,"text":"that our ability to look into the body"},{"time":269000,"text":"in this simple way, using our senses,"},{"time":271000,"text":"is quite recent."},{"time":273000,"text":"The picture I'm showing you is of Leopold Auenbrugger"},{"time":276000,"text":"who, in the late 1700s,"},{"time":278000,"text":"discovered percussion."},{"time":280000,"text":"And the story is that Leopold Auenbrugger"},{"time":283000,"text":"was the son of an innkeeper."},{"time":286000,"text":"And his father used to go down into the basement"},{"time":289000,"text":"to tap on the sides of casks of wine"},{"time":291000,"text":"to determine how much wine was left"},{"time":293000,"text":"and whether to reorder."},{"time":295000,"text":"And so when Auenbrugger became a physician,"},{"time":297000,"text":"he began to do the same thing."},{"time":299000,"text":"He began to tap on the chests of his patients,"},{"time":302000,"text":"on their abdomens."},{"time":304000,"text":"And basically everything we know about percussion,"},{"time":306000,"text":"which you can think of as an ultrasound of its day --"},{"time":310000,"text":"organ enlargement, fluid around the heart, fluid in the lungs,"},{"time":313000,"text":"abdominal changes --"},{"time":315000,"text":"all of this he described in this wonderful manuscript"},{"time":317000,"text":"\"Inventum Novum,\" \"New Invention,\""},{"time":320000,"text":"which would have disappeared into obscurity,"},{"time":322000,"text":"except for the fact that this physician, Corvisart,"},{"time":325000,"text":"a famous French physician --"},{"time":327000,"text":"famous only because he was physician to this gentleman --"},{"time":330000,"text":"Corvisart repopularized and reintroduced the work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334000,"text":"And it was followed a year or two later"},{"time":336000,"text":"by Laennec discovering the stethoscope."},{"time":339000,"text":"Laennec, it is said, was walking in the streets of Paris"},{"time":342000,"text":"and saw two children playing with a stick."},{"time":344000,"text":"One was scratching at the end of the stick,"},{"time":347000,"text":"another child listened at the other end."},{"time":349000,"text":"And Laennec thought this would be a wonderful way"},{"time":351000,"text":"to listen to the chest or listen to the abdomen"},{"time":353000,"text":"using what he called \"the cylinder.\""},{"time":355000,"text":"Later he renamed it the stethoscope."},{"time":357000,"text":"And that is how stethoscope and auscultation was born."},{"time":361000,"text":"So within a few years,"},{"time":363000,"text":"in the late 1800s, early 1900s,"},{"time":365000,"text":"all of a sudden,"},{"time":367000,"text":"the barber surgeon had given way"},{"time":370000,"text":"to the physician who was trying to make a diagnosis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"If you'll recall, prior to that time,"},{"time":375000,"text":"no matter what ailed you, you went to see the barber surgeon"},{"time":378000,"text":"who wound up cupping you,"},{"time":380000,"text":"bleeding you, purging you."},{"time":382000,"text":"And, oh yes, if you wanted,"},{"time":384000,"text":"he would give you a haircut -- short on the sides, long in the back --"},{"time":387000,"text":"and pull your tooth while he was at it."},{"time":389000,"text":"He made no attempt at diagnosis."},{"time":391000,"text":"In fact, some of you might well know"},{"time":393000,"text":"that the barber pole, the red and white stripes,"},{"time":396000,"text":"represents the blood bandages of the barber surgeon,"},{"time":399000,"text":"and the receptacles on either end"},{"time":401000,"text":"represent the pots in which the blood was collected."},{"time":404000,"text":"But the arrival of auscultation and percussion"},{"time":407000,"text":"represented a sea change,"},{"time":409000,"text":"a moment when physicians were beginning to look inside the body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412000,"text":"And this particular painting, I think,"},{"time":415000,"text":"represents the pinnacle, the peak, of that clinical era."},{"time":418000,"text":"This is a very famous painting:"},{"time":420000,"text":"\"The Doctor\" by Luke Fildes."},{"time":423000,"text":"Luke Fildes was commissioned to paint this by Tate,"},{"time":426000,"text":"who then established the Tate Gallery."},{"time":428000,"text":"And Tate asked Fildes to paint a painting"},{"time":430000,"text":"of social importance."},{"time":432000,"text":"And it's interesting that Fildes picked this topic."},{"time":435000,"text":"Fildes' oldest son, Philip,"},{"time":438000,"text":"died at the age of nine on Christmas Eve"},{"time":441000,"text":"after a brief illness."},{"time":443000,"text":"And Fildes was so taken by the physician"},{"time":446000,"text":"who held vigil at the bedside for two, three nights,"},{"time":450000,"text":"that he decided that he would try and depict"},{"time":452000,"text":"the physician in our time --"},{"time":454000,"text":"almost a tribute to this physician."},{"time":456000,"text":"And hence the painting \"The Doctor,\" a very famous painting."},{"time":459000,"text":"It's been on calendars, postage stamps in many different countries."},{"time":462000,"text":"I've often wondered, what would Fildes have done"},{"time":465000,"text":"had he been asked to paint this painting"},{"time":467000,"text":"in the modern era,"},{"time":469000,"text":"in the year 2011?"},{"time":472000,"text":"Would he have substituted a computer screen"},{"time":476000,"text":"for where he had the patient?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":478000,"text":"I've gotten into some trouble in Silicon Valley"},{"time":480000,"text":"for saying that the patient in the bed"},{"time":482000,"text":"has almost become an icon"},{"time":485000,"text":"for the real patient who's in the computer."},{"time":488000,"text":"I've actually coined a term for that entity in the computer."},{"time":491000,"text":"I call it the iPatient."},{"time":493000,"text":"The iPatient is getting wonderful care all across America."},{"time":496000,"text":"The real patient often wonders,"},{"time":498000,"text":"where is everyone?"},{"time":500000,"text":"When are they going to come by and explain things to me?"},{"time":503000,"text":"Who's in charge?"},{"time":505000,"text":"There's a real disjunction between the patient's perception"},{"time":508000,"text":"and our own perceptions as physicians of the best medical care."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511000,"text":"I want to show you a picture"},{"time":513000,"text":"of what rounds looked like"},{"time":515000,"text":"when I was in training."},{"time":517000,"text":"The focus was around the patient."},{"time":519000,"text":"We went from bed to bed. The attending physician was in charge."},{"time":522000,"text":"Too often these days,"},{"time":524000,"text":"rounds look very much like this,"},{"time":526000,"text":"where the discussion is taking place"},{"time":528000,"text":"in a room far away from the patient."},{"time":531000,"text":"The discussion is all about images on the computer, data."},{"time":534000,"text":"And the one critical piece missing"},{"time":536000,"text":"is that of the patient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538000,"text":"Now I've been influenced in this thinking"},{"time":541000,"text":"by two anecdotes that I want to share with you."},{"time":544000,"text":"One had to do with a friend of mine who had a breast cancer,"},{"time":547000,"text":"had a small breast cancer detected --"},{"time":550000,"text":"had her lumpectomy in the town in which I lived."},{"time":552000,"text":"This is when I was in Texas."},{"time":554000,"text":"And she then spent a lot of time researching"},{"time":557000,"text":"to find the best cancer center in the world"},{"time":560000,"text":"to get her subsequent care."},{"time":562000,"text":"And she found the place and decided to go there, went there."},{"time":565000,"text":"Which is why I was surprised a few months later"},{"time":568000,"text":"to see her back in our own town,"},{"time":571000,"text":"getting her subsequent care with her private oncologist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574000,"text":"And I pressed her, and I asked her,"},{"time":576000,"text":"\"Why did you come back and get your care here?\""},{"time":579000,"text":"And she was reluctant to tell me."},{"time":581000,"text":"She said, \"The cancer center was wonderful."},{"time":584000,"text":"It had a beautiful facility,"},{"time":586000,"text":"giant atrium, valet parking,"},{"time":588000,"text":"a piano that played itself,"},{"time":590000,"text":"a concierge that took you around from here to there."},{"time":593000,"text":"But,\" she said,"},{"time":595000,"text":"\"but they did not touch my breasts.\""},{"time":599000,"text":"Now you and I could argue"},{"time":601000,"text":"that they probably did not need to touch her breasts."},{"time":603000,"text":"They had her scanned inside out."},{"time":605000,"text":"They understood her breast cancer at the molecular level;"},{"time":608000,"text":"they had no need to touch her breasts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610000,"text":"But to her, it mattered deeply."},{"time":613000,"text":"It was enough for her to make the decision"},{"time":617000,"text":"to get her subsequent care with her private oncologist"},{"time":620000,"text":"who, every time she went,"},{"time":622000,"text":"examined both breasts including the axillary tail,"},{"time":625000,"text":"examined her axilla carefully,"},{"time":627000,"text":"examined her cervical region, her inguinal region,"},{"time":629000,"text":"did a thorough exam."},{"time":631000,"text":"And to her, that spoke of a kind of attentiveness that she needed."},{"time":635000,"text":"I was very influenced by that anecdote."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637000,"text":"I was also influenced by another experience that I had,"},{"time":640000,"text":"again, when I was in Texas, before I moved to Stanford."},{"time":643000,"text":"I had a reputation"},{"time":645000,"text":"as being interested in patients"},{"time":647000,"text":"with chronic fatigue."},{"time":650000,"text":"This is not a reputation you would wish on your worst enemy."},{"time":654000,"text":"I say that because these are difficult patients."},{"time":657000,"text":"They have often been rejected by their families,"},{"time":660000,"text":"have had bad experiences with medical care"},{"time":662000,"text":"and they come to you fully prepared"},{"time":665000,"text":"for you to join the long list of people"},{"time":667000,"text":"who's about to disappoint them."},{"time":669000,"text":"And I learned very early on with my first patient"},{"time":672000,"text":"that I could not do justice"},{"time":674000,"text":"to this very complicated patient"},{"time":676000,"text":"with all the records they were bringing"},{"time":678000,"text":"in a new patient visit of 45 minutes."},{"time":680000,"text":"There was just no way."},{"time":682000,"text":"And if I tried, I'd disappoint them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685000,"text":"And so I hit on this method"},{"time":687000,"text":"where I invited the patient"},{"time":689000,"text":"to tell me the story for their entire first visit,"},{"time":692000,"text":"and I tried not to interrupt them."},{"time":695000,"text":"We know the average American physician"},{"time":697000,"text":"interrupts their patient in 14 seconds."},{"time":700000,"text":"And if I ever get to heaven,"},{"time":702000,"text":"it will be because I held my piece for 45 minutes"},{"time":705000,"text":"and did not interrupt my patient."},{"time":707000,"text":"I then scheduled the physical exam for two weeks hence,"},{"time":710000,"text":"and when the patient came for the physical,"},{"time":712000,"text":"I was able to do a thorough physical,"},{"time":714000,"text":"because I had nothing else to do."},{"time":716000,"text":"I like to think that I do a thorough physical exam,"},{"time":719000,"text":"but because the whole visit was now about the physical,"},{"time":722000,"text":"I could do an extraordinarily thorough exam."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725000,"text":"And I remember my very first patient in that series"},{"time":729000,"text":"continued to tell me more history"},{"time":731000,"text":"during what was meant to be the physical exam visit."},{"time":734000,"text":"And I began my ritual."},{"time":736000,"text":"I always begin with the pulse,"},{"time":738000,"text":"then I examine the hands, then I look at the nail beds,"},{"time":741000,"text":"then I slide my hand up to the epitrochlear node,"},{"time":743000,"text":"and I was into my ritual."},{"time":745000,"text":"And when my ritual began,"},{"time":747000,"text":"this very voluble patient"},{"time":749000,"text":"began to quiet down."},{"time":751000,"text":"And I remember having a very eerie sense"},{"time":754000,"text":"that the patient and I"},{"time":757000,"text":"had slipped back into a primitive ritual"},{"time":759000,"text":"in which I had a role"},{"time":761000,"text":"and the patient had a role."},{"time":763000,"text":"And when I was done,"},{"time":765000,"text":"the patient said to me with some awe,"},{"time":767000,"text":"\"I have never been examined like this before.\""},{"time":770000,"text":"Now if that were true,"},{"time":772000,"text":"it's a true condemnation of our health care system,"},{"time":774000,"text":"because they had been seen in other places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":777000,"text":"I then proceeded to tell the patient,"},{"time":779000,"text":"once the patient was dressed,"},{"time":781000,"text":"the standard things that the person must have heard in other institutions,"},{"time":784000,"text":"which is, \"This is not in your head."},{"time":786000,"text":"This is real."},{"time":788000,"text":"The good news, it's not cancer, it's not tuberculosis,"},{"time":791000,"text":"it's not coccidioidomycosis or some obscure fungal infection."},{"time":794000,"text":"The bad news is we don't know exactly what's causing this,"},{"time":797000,"text":"but here's what you should do, here's what we should do.\""},{"time":800000,"text":"And I would lay out all the standard treatment options"},{"time":803000,"text":"that the patient had heard elsewhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806000,"text":"And I always felt"},{"time":808000,"text":"that if my patient gave up the quest"},{"time":810000,"text":"for the magic doctor, the magic treatment"},{"time":813000,"text":"and began with me on a course towards wellness,"},{"time":816000,"text":"it was because I had earned the right"},{"time":818000,"text":"to tell them these things"},{"time":820000,"text":"by virtue of the examination."},{"time":822000,"text":"Something of importance had transpired in the exchange."},{"time":826000,"text":"I took this to my colleagues"},{"time":828000,"text":"at Stanford in anthropology"},{"time":830000,"text":"and told them the same story."},{"time":832000,"text":"And they immediately said to me,"},{"time":834000,"text":"\"Well you are describing a classic ritual.\""},{"time":836000,"text":"And they helped me understand"},{"time":838000,"text":"that rituals are all about transformation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841000,"text":"We marry, for example,"},{"time":843000,"text":"with great pomp and ceremony and expense"},{"time":846000,"text":"to signal our departure"},{"time":848000,"text":"from a life of solitude and misery and loneliness"},{"time":850000,"text":"to one of eternal bliss."},{"time":853000,"text":"I'm not sure why you're laughing."},{"time":855000,"text":"That was the original intent, was it not?"},{"time":857000,"text":"We signal transitions of power"},{"time":859000,"text":"with rituals."},{"time":861000,"text":"We signal the passage of a life with rituals."},{"time":863000,"text":"Rituals are terribly important."},{"time":865000,"text":"They're all about transformation."},{"time":867000,"text":"Well I would submit to you"},{"time":869000,"text":"that the ritual"},{"time":871000,"text":"of one individual coming to another"},{"time":873000,"text":"and telling them things"},{"time":875000,"text":"that they would not tell their preacher or rabbi,"},{"time":878000,"text":"and then, incredibly on top of that,"},{"time":880000,"text":"disrobing and allowing touch --"},{"time":883000,"text":"I would submit to you that that is a ritual of exceeding importance."},{"time":887000,"text":"And if you shortchange that ritual"},{"time":889000,"text":"by not undressing the patient,"},{"time":891000,"text":"by listening with your stethoscope on top of the nightgown,"},{"time":894000,"text":"by not doing a complete exam,"},{"time":896000,"text":"you have bypassed on the opportunity"},{"time":898000,"text":"to seal the patient-physician relationship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902000,"text":"I am a writer,"},{"time":904000,"text":"and I want to close by reading you a short passage that I wrote"},{"time":908000,"text":"that has to do very much with this scene."},{"time":910000,"text":"I'm an infectious disease physician,"},{"time":912000,"text":"and in the early days of HIV, before we had our medications,"},{"time":915000,"text":"I presided over so many scenes like this."},{"time":919000,"text":"I remember, every time I went to a patient's deathbed,"},{"time":922000,"text":"whether in the hospital or at home,"},{"time":924000,"text":"I remember my sense of failure --"},{"time":928000,"text":"the feeling of I don't know what I have to say;"},{"time":930000,"text":"I don't know what I can say;"},{"time":932000,"text":"I don't know what I'm supposed to do."},{"time":934000,"text":"And out of that sense of failure,"},{"time":936000,"text":"I remember, I would always examine the patient."},{"time":939000,"text":"I would pull down the eyelids."},{"time":941000,"text":"I would look at the tongue."},{"time":943000,"text":"I would percuss the chest. I would listen to the heart."},{"time":946000,"text":"I would feel the abdomen."},{"time":948000,"text":"I remember so many patients,"},{"time":951000,"text":"their names still vivid on my tongue,"},{"time":953000,"text":"their faces still so clear."},{"time":955000,"text":"I remember so many huge, hollowed out, haunted eyes"},{"time":959000,"text":"staring up at me as I performed this ritual."},{"time":962000,"text":"And then the next day,"},{"time":964000,"text":"I would come, and I would do it again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":966000,"text":"And I wanted to read you this one closing passage"},{"time":969000,"text":"about one patient."},{"time":971000,"text":"\"I recall one patient"},{"time":973000,"text":"who was at that point"},{"time":975000,"text":"no more than a skeleton"},{"time":977000,"text":"encased in shrinking skin,"},{"time":979000,"text":"unable to speak,"},{"time":981000,"text":"his mouth crusted with candida"},{"time":983000,"text":"that was resistant to the usual medications."},{"time":986000,"text":"When he saw me"},{"time":988000,"text":"on what turned out to be his last hours on this earth,"},{"time":990000,"text":"his hands moved as if in slow motion."},{"time":993000,"text":"And as I wondered what he was up to,"},{"time":995000,"text":"his stick fingers made their way"},{"time":997000,"text":"up to his pajama shirt,"},{"time":999000,"text":"fumbling with his buttons."},{"time":1002000,"text":"I realized that he was wanting"},{"time":1004000,"text":"to expose his wicker-basket chest to me."},{"time":1007000,"text":"It was an offering, an invitation."},{"time":1010000,"text":"I did not decline."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1012000,"text":"I percussed. I palpated. I listened to the chest."},{"time":1015000,"text":"I think he surely must have known by then"},{"time":1017000,"text":"that it was vital for me"},{"time":1019000,"text":"just as it was necessary for him."},{"time":1021000,"text":"Neither of us could skip this ritual,"},{"time":1024000,"text":"which had nothing to do with detecting rales in the lung,"},{"time":1027000,"text":"or finding the gallop rhythm of heart failure."},{"time":1030000,"text":"No, this ritual was about the one message"},{"time":1033000,"text":"that physicians have needed to convey to their patients."},{"time":1036000,"text":"Although, God knows, of late, in our hubris,"},{"time":1038000,"text":"we seem to have drifted away."},{"time":1040000,"text":"We seem to have forgotten --"},{"time":1042000,"text":"as though, with the explosion of knowledge,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"the whole human genome mapped out at our feet,"},{"time":1047000,"text":"we are lulled into inattention,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"forgetting that the ritual is cathartic to the physician,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"necessary for the patient --"},{"time":1054000,"text":"forgetting that the ritual has meaning"},{"time":1056000,"text":"and a singular message to convey to the patient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1060000,"text":"And the message, which I didn't fully understand then,"},{"time":1063000,"text":"even as I delivered it,"},{"time":1065000,"text":"and which I understand better now is this:"},{"time":1068000,"text":"I will always, always, always be there."},{"time":1071000,"text":"I will see you through this."},{"time":1073000,"text":"I will never abandon you."},{"time":1075000,"text":"I will be with you through the end.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1077000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}